    {
      "id": "3a3c06694f62db71174c3cc050b9d8ff5b32c95d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-19 11:55:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)\n\nI won't +/-1 since you have your two +1s already, but personally, I'd clean up the language and overall status of using the \"--tag\" argument since somebody actually using it will at best obtain unexpected results rather than a clear indication that it's no longer supported.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "982fe74ebb558b123dad4815ed6f874063ffef16",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-22 21:49:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBrian, I _can't_ remove --tag because the Intel build farm relies on it being there, and doing nothing.\n\nI think that deprecated is an accurate word in this context.  It is exactly as funtional as it was before this patch, and remains to support your build farm.  Granted, it has done nothing-at-all for quite some time.  But apparently nothing-at-all was desired functionality.\n\nBut this not lets _you_ guys know that your build farm is relying on a tag which, in the future, will go away.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "28f779f7d331eca7e971c4ccdd7c974d9d648d58",
      "author": {
